package main

// Soundness regression: a borrowed slice *reassigned* (not init-bound) into
// a returned local must still record its alias, so a LOCAL reaching that
// return through a call is rejected. f reassigns a sub-slice of its borrowed
// parameter into t and returns t — inference must record ReturnAliases=[[0]]
// for f. evil then passes a LOCAL array into f; the local reaches f's
// returned slot through the call, and the call-expansion in alias_set must
// reject it. Before the fix the Assignment path under-recorded f's alias
// (empty set), and evil compiled — a dangling slice into a dead frame.
fn f(a byte[]) byte[] {
	var t byte[]
	t = a[0:1]
	return t
}

fn evil(a byte[]) byte[] {
	var loc byte[16]
	return f(loc[:])
}

fn main() {}
